<DOCNO>GH950816-000025</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950816-000025</DOCID>
<DATE>950816</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Top open</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976863258</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Perth Badminton Open from September 1 to 3 not only boasts the
biggest prize fund on the Friends Provident British Grand Slam Tour but
will also feature all the country's leading players.
The organisers confirmed yesterday that former European champion
Darren Hall and Jo Muggeridge will defend their singles titles.
National champions Bruce Flockhart and Anne Gibson will head the
Scottish contenders in the run-up to team selection for next year's
Olympics in Atlanta, with only the top two players sure of a place in
the team.
</TEXT>
