<HEADLINE>Solid background of distinctive style</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>LUCY LOCKHART</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Advertising Feature</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>SCOTLANDS HOMES,</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976863269</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
INDIVIDUALITY is the keynote where Tilbury Douglas is concerned. It is
the company's proud boast that it has no fewer than 17 different house
styles incorporating a variety of interesting brick types, a range of
window styles and distinctive features such as cornerstones, rendering
and pediments, on its 13 existing and seven planned new sites around
Scotland.
But innovative though this builder most certainly is, its philosophy
remains solidly old fashioned in the best sense. Not for them the speed
and convenience of timber-frame construction. Instead they prefer to use
the traditional brick-by-brick (and more of them too) skills of earlier
eras, to create homes of quality and distinction.
''Our traditional building methods may take a little longer, but the
finished result is well worth it,'' declares Jan Jeram, sales and
marketing director for Tilbury Douglas.
''The interiors are further proof of our quality, with their generous
proportions, modern comforts such as central heating and double glazed
windows, plus good storage facilities.''
Currently Ms Jeram explains: ''We have a lot of sites under
construction, and many new ones coming on stream. We recently replanned
all of the exterior finishes of our houses and introduced a lot of new
elevations -- they are the same houses inside, but it's made them more
attractive and appealing. That has proved to be very successful. We have
had a very good year so far, and we look to increasing that success as
soon as things get back to normal after the holidays.''
In an extremely competitive marketplace, Tilbury Douglas has been
making strenuous efforts to satisfy the demands of their customers,
coming up with incentive packages, tailor-made both to individual sites
and individual purchasers.
On the company's Wallace Glen development for example, it has seen
around 20 houses sold over a two-month period, following the
introduction of a #4000 furniture voucher. Purchasers taking advantage
of the offer, have been able to select furniture to that value from Reid
Furniture.
''It's our policy,'' comments Jan Jeram, ''to make it as easy as
possible for people to purchase one of our houses and with this offer
they can treat themselves to furniture for their new home.''
One of the most recent developments, The Nursery at Law, Lanarkshire,
is a community of 60 one-bedroomed cottage flats and two and
three-bedroomed villas. With prices starting from #31,995 Jan Jeram
forecasts: ''We expect The Nursery to be very popular given its central
location. Together with the quality and competitive prices of the homes,
it is likely to have strong appeal.''
So what does the company have on offer around its sites just now?
At Cumbernauld, The Cedars offers two and three-bedroomed
semi-detached villas from #54,995; three-bedroomed semi-detached
bungalows from #74,495; and three and four-bedroomed detached villas
starting at #80,495. The Green at Johnstone has three and four-bedroomed
semi-villas from #63,750, while at Baillieston, Springhill Park, offers
two and three-bedroomed villas from #52,490 with two and three-bedroomed
semi-villas from #61,495.
Paisley's Abercorn Estate has one, two and three-bedroomed homes from
#28,495 while at Beith, Alder Grove's three-bedroomed detached bungalows
start from #75,995; with three and four-bedroomed villas offered from
#70,965.
At Ayr, Heathfield has two and three-bedroomed semi-villas from
#54,995 with three and four-bedroomed detached villas from #77,995 while
at Troon, The Fairways has three-bedroomed semis from #61,495. Avongrove
at Strathaven offers two-bedroomed terraced villas from #48,995 while in
Central Region Stirling's aforementioned Wallace Glen, Broomridge,
offers two and three-bedroomed semi-villas from #58,995 and three and
four-bedroomed detached villas from #75,495.
Not far away New Carron Village at Falkirk, gives a choice of two and
three-bedroomed terraced/semi-villas from #50,995 with three and
four-bedroomed detached villas starting from #69,995.
</TEXT>
