<TEXT>
EDUCATION chiefs in Grampian are taking swift action to ensure that
school pupils cannot tap into pornography on the Internet. Depute
director of education Bruce Robertson told councillors yesterday the
speed with which the global computer network is expanding made it
essential that Grampian provide schools with policy and guidance on its
use. With the Education committee's approval, he now plans a circular to
be sent out to all heads of educational establishments. Internet
Providers are to filter the choice of materials to which pupils can get
access but depute director of education Bruce Robertson said back-up
supervision would also be required.
