<TEXT>
Dorset Community NHS Trust was fined #14,000 yesterday over the death
of a severely handicapped patient who drowned in a bath at a nursing
home, after a care assistant left her to prepare Sunday lunch.
Margaret Smallwood died in 6in of water, last November, at The Gables
Nursing Home, in Weymouth, Dorset. The trust admitted failing to ensure
her safety, contrary to Section 3 of the 1974 Health and Safety at Work
Act.
