<HEADLINE>Cervical cancer deaths fall</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976863356</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MORE women in Glasgow are contracting cervical cancer but the death
rate from it has decreased slightly, according to figures issued by
Greater Glasgow Health Board.
The board says that in 1993, the most recent year for which full data
is available, 89 women were registered as having cervical cancer
compared to 76 new cases the previous year. However, deaths from the
cancer in 1993 had gone down to 29 from 32 in 1992.
