<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950816-000163</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950816-000163</DOCID>
<DATE>950816</DATE>
<HEADLINE>In love with the idea alone</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976863397</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FILM star Britt Ekland posed beside a sculpture of runaway lovers at
Gretna Green yesterday and scotched any talk of a third marriage for
herself.
Opening a new sculpture park at Gretna, Ms Ekland, 53, said she would
have loved to have been married over the blacksmith's anvil.
''It's a fabulous idea. No contracts, no politics, just bang and
you're married,'' she said, before quickly adding: ''but my marrying
days are over''.
The Swedish-born actress's two marriages -- to the late actor Peter
Sellers and to drummer Jim MacDonnell -- were dissolved.
The Gretna sculptures include several on a romantic theme, including
The Runaway Lovers by John Tonks, of Worcester.
They are the work of nine amateur and eight professional sculptors who
attend Birmingham University.
Three of the sculptures have been commissioned as permanent features
and the rest are for sale.
</TEXT>
